FEATURE ARTICLE
=================
MAGAZINE INDUSTRY WANTS TO GAIN AD WEIGHT IN 2002
By Linnea Anderson, Writer
Still reeling from the one-two combination of the dot-com collapse
and September 11, the magazine industry is looking to get its legs
back in 2002. The dearth of advertising pages in 2001 was a sharp
contrast to 2000, when, flush with advertising dollars from the
tech sector, many publications were as thick as phone books and
rolling in revenue. Read more.http://Hoovers.ym0.net/re3.asp?c=34673&p=109912&e=27946744 ===========
Site Tips
===========
BUSINESS BONEYARD
Have you ever wondered "what ever happened to Excite, Inc.?"
Hoover's maintains a database of companies acquired or no longer
in operation. We call that database the "Business Boneyard." May
your searches never reach a dead end ....
Search the Business Boneyard.http://Hoovers.ym0.net/re3.asp?c=34673&p=109922&e=27946744 HOOVER'S 25 MOST-VIEWED COMPANIES
When companies are highlighted in the business pages and on TV,
subscribers turn to Hoover's to get complete background coverage.
Find out which companies are garnering the most clicks on Hoover's
Top 25 Most-Viewed Companies.http://Hoovers.ym0.net/re3.asp?c=34673&p=109914&e=27946744 =============
Search Tips
=============
UNDERSTANDING HOOVER'S SEARCH RESULTS
When you perform a Company Name search, the "Hoover's Matches"
section of your results can contain up to three types of
companies: those Matching, Similar To, and Related To your query.
Suppose you want to research the company that brews Red Stripe
Beer, but you don't know its name. Find out how.http://Hoovers.ym0.net/re3.asp?c=34673&p=109910&e=27946744 USE D?MATCHES TO BRING YOUR SEARCH TO THE LOCAL LEVEL
Continuing with the beverage industry, suppose you want to make a
sales call to each location of Guinness Import Co. in the United
States (Guinness/UDV brews Red Stripe Beer). Find out how.http://Hoovers.ym0.net/re3.asp?c=34673&p=109911&e=27946744 ==========================
